            <h1>Redefining the African Hope</h1>
            <p>$150 billion is spent annually on global aid, yet poverty still remains.</p>
            <p>
                All that money. And still no relief. Something's not working. We believe the traditional relief model is
                the problem - increasing people's dependency on charity rather than freeing them from it.
            </p>
            <p>
                Hoopo (formerly known as PRICE) is a social enterprise that transforms impoverished communities through
                the power of work. Our unique investment model creates jobs that break the reliance on handouts, while
                delivering a return to our supporters as well. We put your kindness where it counts.
            </p>



